<p>Costa et al. (1998) concluded that 'lethal skeletal dysplasia with gracile bones' is probably a heterogeneous disorder. Most of the possible cases have been sporadic; the history of parental consanguinity in some cases has raised the possibility of autosomal recessive inheritance.</p>

<p>[Costa, T., Azouz, E. M., Fitzpatrick, J., Kamel-Reid, S., Smith, C. R., Silver, M. M. Skeletal dysplasias with gracile bones: three new cases, including two offspring of a mother with a dwarfing condition. Am. J. Med. Genet. 76: 125-132, 1998.]<br/></p>